{
  "stem": "9503.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, you know, this is the same mother who had brought me up as a-- a good child, you know, religious, good, moral, and all that.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she said, I really think it would be a good idea, and she actually set me up.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because in my ski pants, which were-- had elastic at the bottom, sort of poofy, bell bottom or whatever you call that, she made a slit in the pocket so that I could grab some potatoes and put them in the pocket.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they would roll down to the bottom, and I wouldn't look very suspicious.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I-- I remember doing this a couple times, and I was absolutely frightened out of my, you know, wits.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But-- but but these were-- were things that made this period so abnormal, because all the norms that one grew up with, moral norms, seem to-- or not all but many of them, seem to have gone by the wayside.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] There was an incident [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] where my mother-- this was after my father had left already-- she met a-- a rabbi that she knew from before the war, from Germany, who lived in Theresienstadt with his wife and who was among the more privileged.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They had a privileged class in Theresienstadt.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They had one, I think, probably in every camp.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they invited us for Shabbat, for Friday night, and we thought we were invited to their room.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Well, we were not.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We were invited to their door to watch them light the candles, and then we were dismissed.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I remember my mother's reaction.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "She was absolutely incensed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And-- and incidentally, my mother, after the war, really lost our religion.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
